  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tier naming:</strong> Use clear, hierarchical names (Basic, Pro, Enterprise) that indicate value progression.</li>
        <li><strong>Feature ordering:</strong> List features in order of importance. Lead with the most compelling features.</li>
        <li><strong>Highlight recommended:</strong> Always highlight one tier as recommended. This guides user decisions and improves conversion.</li>
        <li><strong>CTAs:</strong> Use primary buttons for the recommended plan and secondary buttons for others. Use "Contact Sales" for enterprise tiers.</li>
        <li><strong>Pricing transparency:</strong> Show all costs upfront. If there are per-user or usage-based costs, make them clear.</li>
        <li><strong>Yearly savings:</strong> When offering discounts for annual billing, display the savings prominently (e.g., "Save 20%").</li>
        <li><strong>Comparison tables:</strong> Use tables for detailed feature comparisons. Cards work better for quick overviews.</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile considerations:</strong> Cards stack naturally on mobile. Tables may need horizontal scrolling.</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Use proper table semantics with <code>scope</code> attributes. Ensure toggle has proper labeling.</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

